      "review_summary": "The branch recomputes known-priced transcript entries with zero recorded cost and nonzero tokens, clears stale cost breakdowns for summaries/session logs, bumps the usage-cost cache version to 5, and adds regression coverage.\n\nPR surface: Source +23, Tests +68. Total +91 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. for a source-level reproduction: current main parses usage.cost.total 0 into costTotal/costBreakdown and only estimates flat pricing when costTotal is undefined, so known-priced nonzero DeepSeek V4 usage can remain zero. I did not run a live DeepSeek API call in this read-only review.",
