        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Estimate known zero transcript costs",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nFixes #97047.\r\n\r\nDeepSeek V4 compatible API transcripts can record `usage.cost.total` as `0` even when token usage is present. OpenClaw trusted that zero, so Control UI Spend and session summaries could show known-priced DeepSeek V4 usage as free.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\n`src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts` now treats a recorded zero total as stale when the model has known pricing and non-zero token usage, then recomputes the estimate through the existing pricing path. The cost cache version was bumped so stale zero-cost summaries are refreshed, while unknown-pricing zero totals still remain missing-cost entries.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\n\r\nSpend totals and session logs now show an estimated cost for known-priced DeepSeek V4 usage instead of silently reporting zero. Existing cached summaries are refreshed by the version bump.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\nAfter fix\r\n<img width=\"1437\" height=\"736\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b77fe828-117c-44ec-921a-5b8cd516358f\" />\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1447\" height=\"746\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c95f9b5e-b20c-406a-85ca-6aa49dc2ce84\" />\r\n\r\n",
